com.legacy.structure_gel.access_helpers

Class JigsawAccessHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.legacy.structure_gel.access_helpers.JigsawAccessHelper

  • public class JigsawAccessHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains methods to access normally privated values in the jigsaw piece or registry. Also allows for you to add to/remove from existing JigsawPatterns, allowing you to add new houses to villages, change pillager outpost designs, etc.
    Author:
    David

        public static void addIllagerStructures(net.minecraft.world.gen.feature.structure.Structure<?>... structures)
        The Structure.field_236384_t_ list allows for villages and pillager outposts to generate terrain underneath them so they don't float. The area that gets generated is based on the structure that starts the generation. In villages, this would be the town center.
